Dark matter is a mysterious cosmic phenomenon that accounts for 27 percent of all matter and energy. Though dark matter is all around us  we cannot see it or feel it. But scientists can infer the presence of dark matter by looking at how normal matter behaves around it.doesnt Galaxy clusters  which consist of thousands of galaxies  are important for exploring dark matter.
